Name: Contact Persona
Options: Decision Maker

Name: AI-powered summary
Description: A multi-line text field for storing AI-generated summaries or insights related to the contact

Name: Communication notes
Description: Multi-line notes capturing details about communications with the contact

Name: Outreach strategy
Description: Detailed notes describing the contact's outreach strategy, including messaging approach, channels, and cadence.

Name: Value drivers
Description: Key factors or reasons that drive value for this contact, captured in multi-line text for detailed explanation.

Name: Industry Change Flag
Options: YES; NO

Name: Lead Source Type
Options: referral; inbound; outbound

Name: Average Pageviews
Description: Average number of pageviews per session for this contact. Set automatically.

Name: First Referring Site
Description: URL that referred the contact to your website. Set automatically.

Name: Time First Seen
Description: First time the contact has been seen. Set automatically.

Name: First Touch Converting Campaign
Description: Campaign responsible for the first touch creation of this contact.

Name: First Page Seen
Description: First page the contact visited on your website. Set automatically.

Name: Time of First Session
Description: First time the contact visited your website. Set automatically.

Name: Last Referring Site
Description: Last URL that referred contact to your website. Set automatically.

Name: Time Last Seen
Description: Timestamp for most recent webpage view on your website.

Name: Last Touch Converting Campaign
Description: Campaign responsible for the last touch creation of this contact.

Name: Last Page Seen
Description: Last page the contact visited on your website. Set automatically.

Name: Time of Last Session
Description: Timestamp for start of the most recent session for this contact to your website.

Name: Number of event completions
Description: Total number of events for this contact. Set automatically.

Name: Number of Pageviews
Description: Total number of page views this contact has had on your website. Set automatically.

Name: Number of Sessions
Description: Number of times a contact has come to your website. Set automatically.

Name: Event Revenue
Description: Set event revenue on a contact though the Enterprise Events feature. http://help.hubspot.com/articles/KCS_Article/Reports/How-do-I-create-Events-in-HubSpot

Name: Original Traffic Source
Description: First known source the contact used to find your website. Set automatically, but may be updated manually.

Name: Original Traffic Source Drill-Down 2
Description: Additional information about the source the contact used to find your website. Set automatically.

Description: The source of the latest session for a contact

Name: After-hours contact OK
Description: Indicates whether this contact has given permission to be contacted outside of regular business hours
Options: Yes (true); No (false)

Name: Do not contact - phone
Description: Indicates whether this contact should not be contacted via phone due to their preference or compliance reasons
Options: Yes (true); No (false)

Name: LinkedIn messaging opt-in
Description: Indicates whether the contact has agreed to receive LinkedIn messages
Options: Yes (true); No (false)

Name: Meeting preference
Description: The preferred method of meeting or communication for this contact
Options: Virtual only (virtual_only); Phone only (phone_only); In-person preferred (inperson_preferred); Mixed virtual/in-person (mixed_virtualinperson); No meetings (email only) (no_meetings_email_only)

Name: Secondary communication channel
Description: Backup channel for contacting this contact when primary channel is unresponsive.
Options: Email (email); Phone (phone); SMS/Text (smstext); LinkedIn (linkedin); Video Call (video_call); In-Person (inperson); Chat (chat)

Name: Call recording consent
Description: Indicates whether the contact has provided consent for call recording.
Options: Yes (true); No (false)

Name: Do not contact - email
Description: Indicates whether the contact has requested not to be contacted via email
Options: Yes (true); No (false)

Name: Currently in workflow (discontinued)
Description: True when contact is enrolled in a workflow.
Options: True (true); False (false)

Name: Date of last meeting booked in meetings tool
Description: The date of the last meeting that has been scheduled by a contact through the meetings tool. If multiple meetings have been scheduled, the date of the last chronological meeting in the timeline is shown.

Name: Campaign of last booking in meetings tool
Description: UTM parameter for marketing campaign (e.g. a specific email) responsible for recent meeting booking. Only populated when tracking parameters are included in meeting link.

Name: Medium of last booking in meetings tool
Description: UTM parameter for the channel (e.g. email)  responsible for most recent meeting booking. Only populated when tracking parameters are included in meeting link.

Name: Source of last booking in meetings tool
Description: UTM parameter for the site (e.g. Twitter) responsible for most recent meeting booking. Only populated when tracking parameters are included in meeting link.

Name: First Conversion Date
Description: Date  this  contact  first  submitted  a  form.

Name: First Conversion
Description: First form this contact submitted.

Description: Notes relating to the contact's content membership.

Description: Status of the contact's content membership.
Options: Active (active) [READ-ONLY]; Inactive (inactive) [READ-ONLY]

Name: Last Engagement Date
Description: The last time a contact engaged with your site or a form, document, meetings link, or tracked email. This doesn't include marketing emails or emails to multiple contacts.

Name: Recent Sales Email Clicked Date
Description: The last time a tracked sales email was clicked by this user

Name: Recent Sales Email Opened Date
Description: The last time a tracked sales email was opened by this contact. This property does not update for emails that were sent to more than one contact.

Name: Recent Sales Email Replied Date
Description: The last time a tracked sales email to this contact was replied to. This is set automatically by HubSpot.

Description: A yes/no field that indicates whether the contact is currently in a Sequence.

Description:
When this property is useful:

As a workflow trigger or filter, e.g., “Batch enrichment is Ready” → send this contact’s ID into the batch endpoint.​

As a status marker for reporting (who was included in a batch, who failed, etc.).​
Options: not scheduled; queued; processed; error

Description: Optimal time to contact based on role

Description: Date of Birth

Name: City
Description: A contact's city of residence
Usages: Object requirement (1); Sales view (6); Properties v3 card (1)

Name: Company Name
Description: Name of the contact's company. This can be set independently from the name property on the contact's associated company.
Usages: Inbounddb lists (1); Object requirement (1); Sales view (31); Properties v3 card (2)

Name: Contact Grade
Description:
A+ = Ambassador = more than one referral in the past 12 months
A = Champion = one referral (regardless of outcome) in the past 12 months
B = Potential Champion = I am still determining.
C = Referral who has been referred in the last three years
D = Drip campaign/email blasts from contacts Apollo/Sales Nav/etc.
CB = Current Borrower
PB = Potential Borrower - Somewhere in the loan process.
US = Unsubscribe
X = Delete. There is no chance of moving up the funnel or being unqualified.
H = Harvest
P = Partner
Options: A+; A; B; D; Unsubscribe; Current Borrower  (CB); Potential Borrower (PB); X - Delete (X); Harvest (H)
Usages: Inbounddb lists (1); Sales view (16); Properties v3 card (2)

Name: Content depth
Description:
Env var: SA_QUALITY_LEVEL with values like short, standard, deep.​

In app.py, read it once near the top and adjust prompts:

short → fewer tokens, more direct copy.

standard → what you have now.

deep → ask for more context and allow higher max_tokens.
Options: brief; standard; deep
